items.title: Iraq Construction Report 2024: Investments in Transportation, Renewable Energy, and Housing Infrastructure, Coupled with Increasing Demand for Oil and Gas Projects - Forecast to 2028
items.author: Dublin, Feb. 04, 2025
items.description: The Iraqi construction industry is expected to grow by 5% in 2024, driven by investments in transportation, renewable energy, and housing infrastructure, as well as increasing demand for oil and gas projects. The government has allocated significant funds to the energy, security, and education sectors in the 2024 Fiscal Budget.

insights.sentiment_reasoning: Honeywell, a US-based company, signed a Memorandum of Understanding (MoU) with Iraq's Oil Ministry to develop oil refineries in the country, which is expected to increase the country's crude oil refinery capacity.
